2. Data Processing in the App
The app only processes personal data as necessary and in accordance with the following legal bases under Art. 6 GDPR:

Firebase Authentication: User ID (UID) for login. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR

Cloud Firestore: Stores bingo cards, draw data and UID for managing entries. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR

Local storage (Room): Cards and draws are also stored locally on the device. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR

ML Kit: On-device text recognition. No data is sent to Google servers. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR

Tesseract OCR: Local text recognition using open-source software. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR

OpenCV: Image processing performed locally on the device to improve OCR. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR

AWS Textract (Ultra Scan): Used only after explicit user consent. Images are transmitted in encrypted form to AWS. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR

Google AdMob: Ads are provided via the AdMob SDK. Personalized ads require explicit consent. If declined, non-personalized ads are shown. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR (personalized), Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (non-personalized)

Rewarded Ads: Optional video ads may be watched to unlock one-time benefits. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR

Firebase Analytics & Crashlytics: Used to improve app stability. Only pseudonymized data is processed. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR

Email support: If you contact us by email, your email address and message will be processed. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR

Google Play Billing: Purchases are processed via Google Play. No payment data is stored in the app. Legal basis: Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR

3. Hosting & Data Processing
Data is processed through Google LLC, 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA. Google is certified under the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework. Data is only transferred outside the EU when an adequate level of data protection is ensured under Art. 45 GDPR.

4. Data Retention
User data (e.g., UID and saved cards) is retained until manually deleted by the user. Ad consent can be changed at any time within the app. Support emails are deleted 90 days after resolution. Server logs are anonymized and stored for a maximum of 90 days for technical purposes.

5. Your Rights Under the GDPR
You have the right to access, correct, delete or restrict the processing of your data, to object to processing, and to data portability. You can delete your data directly in the app under “Delete Account & Data”.

6. Changes to This Privacy Policy
This privacy policy may be updated due to legal, technical, or functional changes. The current version is always available in the app.

